Notes:

-This is based on the demo version, so no x64 disassembly.
-Numerous features are still disabled (databases, batch mode, produce ASM, etc) as I don't really use them and it would be quite an effort to stitch them back in.
-Those looking for something similar to the Hex-Rays Decompiler can look into SmartDec. They can provide a linux build on request.
-If you want a full pro version, IDA Pro 5.7 was leaked by APTguy as part of OPERATION &quot;JIuCTOnAD&quot; (DEFOLIATION). Still no GUI for linux users yet :(


This release was built with:

IDA Demo 6.5 Linux (core)
IDA Pro 5.7 Linux (loaders, plugins, procs)
IDA Pro 6.5 Windows (idc, ids, sig, til)
IDA SDK 6.5 (updates)
IDAPython 1.6.0 (added goodie)
